    if checkPerfectCube(result):
        print(f"17 is a perfect cube when multiplied by {m}.")
        break

The execution of this modified code would output nothing because no such `m` exists (an integer greater than 1) that when multiplied with 17 makes a perfect cube. It can be proved mathematically that a prime number, other than 2 and 3, cannot make a perfect cube when multiplied by an integer greater than 1.

